The paper presents a distributed algorithm for performing MAP inference in graphical models, which involves optimization and linear programming. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), which deals with algorithms and techniques for intelligent decision-making. The paper also involves optimization and linear programming, which are common topics in cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The paper's focus on graphs and distributed computation suggests cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) as another possible sub-category. Finally, the paper's application to control systems suggests cs.SY (Systems and Control) as a possible sub-category.
